'''John Samuel Pobee''' (born 9 July 1937) is a [[Ghanaian people|Ghanaian]] [[Christian theology|Christian theologian]] and former [[Vicar General]] of the [[Anglican Diocese of Accra]], [[Ghana]].

== Biography ==
Pobee studied at [[Adisadel College]] (1950-1956), the [[University of Ghana]] (1957-1961), and [[Selwyn College, Cambridge]] (1961-1966). He completed his priestly training at [[Westcott House, Cambridge]] (1963-1964).<ref name="gaas">{{cite web|title=Rev. Professor Emeritus John Samuel Pobee|website=Ghana Academy of Arts and Sciences|url=http://gaas-gh.org/fellowship/membership/rev-professor-emeritus-john-samuel-pobee/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180420093926/http://gaas-gh.org/fellowship/membership/rev-professor-emeritus-john-samuel-pobee/|archive-date=20 April 2018 |accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref> He is presently [[Emeritus Professor]] at the [[University of Ghana]], where he previously taught and served as Head of Department for the Study of Religions and Dean of the Faculty of Arts.<ref name="abc">{{cite web |title=John Samuel Pobee |url=http://www.africanbookscollective.com/authors-editors/john-samuel-pobee |website=African Books Collective |accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>

Pobee is known for his work in the [[New Testament]], [[African Christianity|African Christian]] theology, and [[missiology]]. He has written his [[memoirs]], ''Sense of Grace and Mission'',<ref>{{cite book |last1=Pobee |first1=John S. |title=Sense of Grace and Mission |date=2012 |publisher=African Books Collective |location=Kaneshie-Accra, Ghana |isbn=9789988152284 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mOyeL63VelMC |language=en}}</ref> and a [[festschrift]] was prepared in his honor, entitled ''Trajectories of Religion in Africa''.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Omenyo |first1=Cephas N. |last2=Anum |first2=Eric B. |title=Trajectories of Religion in Africa: Essays in Honour of John S. Pobee |date=2014 |publisher=Rodopi |location=Amsterdam |isbn=9789401210577 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=R_xNAwAAQBAJ |language=en}}</ref>

On 26 July 1994, Pobee married Martha Ama Akyaa Nkrumah, a career diplomat of the Ghana Foreign Service.<ref name="gaas"/>

